			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">@halyavin: Are you sure dynload_win.c is responsible?  It calls SetErrorMode() a second time to reset the flags back to their original value.  (See http://svn.python.org/projects/python/trunk/Python/dynload_win.c)  This should only be a problem in the multi-threaded case.

I also am sceptical that importing ctypes is the problem, because Scons imports it at startup.  (SConstruct imports test_lib.py which, on Windows, imports ctypes.)  I've only seen the flags get reset back some time after startup.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-08-28T16:48:04.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-08-28T16:48:04.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 6 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2968#c6" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2968/comments/full/6" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>